Package agent

Class AgentImplementations

  • java.lang.Object
    • agent.AgentImplementations
  • public class AgentImplementations
extends java.lang.Object
    This class is a container for AgentImp. It acts as an interface to the Environment and Synchronizer packages

      • activateNewPhase

        public void activateNewPhase​(int agentID,
                             boolean next)
        Grants permission to the AgentImp with id agentID to execute the next phase in it's action cycle.
        Parameters:
        agentID - The id of the AgentImp whose next phase should be executed.
        next - Whether or not environment allows the AgentImp involved to execute the next phase in line, or rather execute the same phase again.
